Class SearchFlight

java.lang.Object
bcu.cmp5332.bookingsystem.commands.SearchFlight
All Implemented Interfaces:
Command
public class SearchFlight extends Object implements Command
Command to search flights based on multiple criteria such as origin, destination, departure date range, airline, and flight status.

The search results are displayed in a summarized format, with an option to view detailed information for each matched flight.

      Parameters:
      origin - the origin airport (nullable)
      destination - the destination airport (nullable)

      status - the flight status as string (nullable)

      departureEnd - the end of the departure date range (nullable)

  • Method Details

    • execute

      public void execute(FlightBookingSystem fbs) throws FlightBookingSystemException
      Executes the flight search on the provided FlightBookingSystem instance.

      Matches flights based on the provided criteria and displays short details of matching flights. Offers the user an option to view detailed information for each matched flight.

      Specified by:
      execute in interface Command
      Parameters:
      fbs - the FlightBookingSystem instance
      Throws:
      FlightBookingSystemException - if an invalid flight status is provided
